messages.content: What is the purpose of ComfyUI-S3-Tools?
ComfyUI-S3-Tools is a tool that allows users to load and save files to S3 storage within the ComfyUI interface.
How can a user load a file from S3 using ComfyUI-S3-Tools?
To load a file from S3, the user needs to use the 'Load From S3' function in ComfyUI-S3-Tools.
Is there a visual representation of how to load a file from S3 in ComfyUI-S3-Tools?
Yes, there is an image named 'LoadFromS3.png' that visually represents how to load a file from S3 using ComfyUI-S3-Tools.
How can a user save a file to S3 using ComfyUI-S3-Tools?
To save a file to S3, the user needs to use the 'Save To S3' function in ComfyUI-S3-Tools.
Is there a visual representation of how to save a file to S3 in ComfyUI-S3-Tools?
Yes, there is an image named 'SaveToS3.png' that visually represents how to save a file to S3 using ComfyUI-S3-Tools.
What are the two main functionalities provided by ComfyUI-S3-Tools?
The two main functionalities provided by ComfyUI-S3-Tools are loading files from S3 and saving files to S3.
Does ComfyUI-S3-Tools support both loading from and saving to S3?
Yes, ComfyUI-S3-Tools supports both loading files from S3 and saving files to S3.
